{
  "enabled": true,
  "name": "Execute Test Scripts",
  "description": "Executes all YAML test scripts in e2e-tests/ folder against the running emulator/simulator (Android and/or iOS), takes screenshots at every assertion, and generates an Excel (.xlsx) report with test steps, coverage metrics, and requirement traceability.",
  "version": "2",
  "when": {
    "type": "userTriggered"
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "First ensure openpyxl is installed: run 'pip3 install openpyxl' if not already available. ALSO check if prompt/ folder exists — if it does, read ALL .md files in prompt/ as additional context (credentials, special instructions, flow order, business logic, workarounds). Use this context during test execution for correct data entry, navigation decisions, and expected behavior understanding. Then: 0) Call mobile_list_available_devices to detect ALL available devices (Android and iOS). 1) Check e2e-runs/ for the LATEST run folder (most recent date). If it exists AND has an e2e-test-report.xlsx, open the Excel and read ALL existing Test No. values (column B). Store these as 'already_done' list. RESUME means: skip ANY test case whose Test No. is already in the Excel — NEVER re-run a test that's already recorded. Only execute test cases NOT in the Excel. If all test cases are already in Excel, report 'All test cases already complete' and stop. 2) Create or open the Excel report file (e2e-test-report.xlsx) in the run folder with headers: User Flow, Test No., Test Scenario, Test Steps, Expected Results, Status, Actual Results, Screenshot. INCREMENTAL WRITING: After finishing EACH test case, immediately write its result as a new row in the Excel file (open, append, save). Do NOT wait until module or all tests complete — write per test case so results are saved even if interrupted. Report progress to user per MODULE (not per test case) to avoid noise. BATCH LIMIT: Execute maximum 10 test cases per session. After 10 test cases, STOP gracefully — save Excel, report to user: 'Batch complete: 10 test cases done. X passed, Y failed, Z skipped. Click Execute Test Scripts again to continue with remaining tests.' This prevents hitting the 1000 tool call limit. SKIP AND CONTINUE STRATEGY: If a test or module is BLOCKED (e.g., can't login so post-login tests can't run, element not found, app crashed), mark it as 'Skip' with reason in Actual Results, then MOVE ON to other modules/tests that are NOT dependent on the blocked one. Always maximize test coverage — run everything that CAN be run. Only skip what is truly impossible. PLATFORM-SPECIFIC BEHAVIOR: For Android: use ADB text input (~/Library/Android/sdk/platform-tools/adb -s {device_id} shell input text) for typing — MUST escape special characters (! @ # $ % ^ & *) with backslash. NEVER append '2>&1' to ANY shell command — it causes terminal to hang. This applies to ALL commands: ADB, pip, python, mkdir, etc. Just run commands plain without output redirection. To clear text fields: ONLY use 'adb shell input keyevent KEYCODE_CTRL_A' then 'adb shell input keyevent KEYCODE_DEL' (2 commands, under 1 second). NEVER use KEYCODE_MOVE_HOME + KEYCODE_SHIFT + KEYCODE_MOVE_END or longpress DEL — those are slow. Use mobile_press_button BACK to dismiss keyboard. Disable stylus with 'adb shell settings put secure stylus_handwriting_enabled 0' if needed. For iOS: use mobile_type_keys for text input (works reliably, no escaping needed), dismiss keyboard by tapping outside field or pressing Done, use swipe-right from left edge for back navigation, handle system permission alerts by tapping Allow/Don't Allow. 3) Read all YAML test script files in e2e-tests/ folder. Skip any test cases already in the Excel (resume logic). For EACH remaining test case: a) Check if current device platform matches — skip if not compatible. b) Launch the app fresh (terminate + relaunch). c) Execute each step (tap, type, swipe, assert, clear) using mobile-mcp tools. Use prompt/*.md context for test data and credentials. d) On assert steps, verify with mobile_list_elements_on_screen — call it ONLY ONCE per assertion, never repeat. If element not found on first check, mark as Failed immediately. e) Take screenshot ONLY ONCE per test case — after the FINAL assertion of that test case, not after every single step. Save to run folder screenshots/. EFFICIENCY RULES: Never call list_elements_on_screen more than once per assertion. Never take more than 1 screenshot per test case. Never retry a failed action more than once. If something doesn't work after 1 retry, mark as Failed and move on. f) If a step FAILS or is BLOCKED: mark remaining steps in that test case as the failure reason, write to Excel immediately, then continue to NEXT test case. g) After EACH test case completes (pass, fail, or skip): immediately write that single result row to the Excel file (open, append row, save). 4) After batch complete (10 test cases or all done): finalize the Excel file with metadata header (app name, device(s), date, total pass/fail/skip summary) and apply color coding (green=Passed, red=Failed, yellow=Skip). Actual Results rule: if Passed, copy Expected Results; if Failed, write what actually happened; if Skip, write the reason. 5) Generate metadata.yaml in run folder with date, device info, TC version, pass/fail/skip counts. Report to user: 'Batch complete. X/Y test cases done. Click again to continue.' or 'All test cases complete.' with run folder path and Excel location."
  }
}